cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper presents a new approach to designing deep networks for natural language processing (NLP) using Tensor Product Representations (TPRs). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses deep learning techniques to design internal representations, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses a model for image-caption generation, which could place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new network architecture, which could also make it relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
